{"id":5115,"date":"2012-08-14T15:48:19","date_gmt":"2012-08-14T19:48:19","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=5115"},"modified":"2023-03-24T10:54:06","modified_gmt":"2023-03-24T06:54:06","slug":"allah-continues-forgive","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/14\/allah-continues-forgive\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Tawbah: Allah forgives if they keep repenting"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Huraira reported: The\u00a0Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>A servant committed a sin and he said: O Allah, forgive my sin! Allah Almighty said: My servant has committed a sin and he knows that he has a Lord who forgives sins and holds him accountable. Then, the servant returned to his sin and he said: O Allah, forgive my sin! Allah said: My servant has committed a sin and he knows that he has a Lord who forgives sins and holds him accountable. Then, the servant returned to his sin and he said: O Allah, forgive my sin! Allah said: My servant has committed a sin and he knows that he has a Lord who forgives sins and holds him accountable, so do what you wish as I have forgiven you<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 7507, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2758<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em><strong>Muttafaqun Alayhi<\/strong><\/em>\u00a0(authentic) according to Al-Bukhari and\u00a0Muslim<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0630\u0652\u0646\u064e\u0628\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u064c \u0630\u064e\u0